<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Guides: Finding a guild, Creating a guild, Guild Leadership and more...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Brimstone">Brimstone</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:47 a.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Guides: Finding a guild, Creating a guild, Guild Leadership and more...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>To All People: In a guild, Leading a guild, or Looking for a guild

<P>[The following guides and articles pertain to ANY online gaming clan, guild, order, etc. There are *some* references to Ultima Online and EverQuest, and one of the guides focuses heavily on the Ultima Online universe, however, can be modified for any OnlineRPG (Guide: <a href="http://uoss.stratics.com/strat/guildguide5.htm" target="_top">Organized Guild Warfare</a>).
<P>The other guides, in my opinion, are a must read for anyone who wishes to Lead or Form a guild, Needs help with creating a voting system for new members, needs help with creating policies for membership, or is looking to JOIN or FIND a guild! I have spent hours creating the following guides, and the feedback from those who have read them has been all positive.
<P>I have heard many guilds say that from now on, they will request that all new members read the Guide for Finding a Guild. This guide is VERY helpful for getting players who seek a guild into the proper state of mind.
<P>Without wasting anymore time, let me give you the links to the Guides/Articles I have written for the players of online games, more specifically, Guilds:
<P><b>Guides and Articles for Guilds and Players</b><p><font color="800000">
<BR><a href="http://uoss.stratics.com/strat/guildguide1.htm" target="_top">The Foundation and Birth of your Guild</a>
<BR><a href="http://www.lostorder.com/lostorder/pages/playerguildguide.html" target="_top">Guide to Finding the Perfect Guild</a>
<BR><a href="http://uoss.stratics.com/strat/guildguide2.htm" target="_top">Voting System</a>
<BR><a href="http://uoss.stratics.com/strat/guildguide3.htm" target="_top">Being a Leader</a>
<BR><a href="http://uoss.stratics.com/strat/guildguide4.htm" target="_top">Sample Policy</a>
<BR><a href="http://uoss.stratics.com/strat/guildguide5.htm" target="_top">Organized Guild Warfare</a></font>
<P>All of the above mentioned guides will help to promote healthy, sociable, fun, BONDING guilds and players. That is what online gaming is all about, fun and respect. If you can help me by posting some (or all) of these articles on your web pages, I think that we would see a lot more guilds who focused on healthy roleplaying and PVP, as opposed to much of the crap we see today in online games. I personally will be asking that all new recruits for LOA read the Guide to finding a guild, even if it sways his/her choice for a guild.
<P>Thanks again, everyone, for your support and kind words regarding my articles.
<P><a href="mailto:brimstone@lostorder.com">Brimstone</a>,
<BR><a href="http://www.lostorder.com" target="_top">Lost Order of Akalabeth</a>,
<BR>Founding Father and Chancellor of Communication
<BR>ICQ - 206317
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
